{{infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Exodus | image = Exodus (Starfire) cover.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption =Cover Illustration. | author = [[Steve White (science fiction)|Steve White]] and [[Shirley Meier (science fiction)|Shirley Meier]]<ref name="designers">{{Cite book|author=Shannon Appelcline|title=Designers & Dragons|publisher=[[Mongoose Publishing]]|year=2011| isbn= 978-1-907702-58-7|pages=115}}</ref> | cover_artist = [[Clyde Caldwell]] | country = [[United States]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = [[Starfire (board wargame)#Books|Starfire series]] | genre = [[Science Fiction]] | publisher = [[Baen Books]] | release_date = December 26, 2006 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]], [[Paperback]]) & [[E-book]] | pages = 288 | isbn = 1-4165-2098-8 | oclc= 71329882 | preceded_by = [[Insurrection (Starfire)|Insurrection]] | followed_by = [[Extremis (Starfire)|Extremis]] }}
'''''Exodus''''' is a 2007 [[Military science fiction|military science fiction novel]], and sequel to the "Stars at War" series, written by [[Steve White (science fiction)|Steve White]] and [[Shirley Meier]].
==Plot summary== Advanced aliens depart their homeworld in order to flee their stars impending [[nova]].
Decades after the Terran Civil War the aliens arrive and attempt to colonize an inhabited human world. They are not able to recognize the intelligence of the planet's inhabitants, because they do not recognize human forms of communication as communication.
The miscommunication leads to warfare, where these new aliens throw themselves at their opponents with suicidal fury. The old "anti Bug" alliance partners join together to fight off this new threat.
